description: From sym- +‎ bio- +‎ -genesis. Coined in German by the Russian lichenologist Konstantin Mereschkowski, in a 1910 paper entitled "Theorie der zwei Plasmaarten als Grundlage der Symbiogenesis, einer neuen Lehre von der Entstehung der Organismen."

entries.meaning: (biology) The merging of two separate organisms to form a single new organism.
